Very few groups of insects are known to live on ferns, including the
Heteroptera (
Konstantinov and Knyshov 2015
)
. Within the Heteroptera , there are a handful of clades belonging to the subfamily Bryocorinae (
Namyatova et al. 2016
) that are closely associated with ferns, in particular the tribes Bryocorini (
Konstantinov and Knyshov 2015
) and Felisacini (
Namyatova et al. 2016
). Additionally, a few species of the brocorine tribe Dicyphini are also associated with ferns (
Knight 1938
;
Wheeler et al. 1979
).
